continues_from_previous.notes: in Madrid. But what was my disappointment! The manuscript was undated and bore no other title than: "Quartetto. Boccherini." A careful examination of the quartet convinced me, moreover, that it was spurious: nothing in it reveals the touch, so easily recognizable, of Boccherini'.

partial_notes: This page appears to be the conclusion of entry G.258, containing only final notes about a spurious quartet manuscript found in Madrid and its unpublished status.
